House Resolution 721
By: Representatives Myles of the 126th and Howard of the 129th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Reverend Anthony Maurice Booker; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Reverend Anthony Maurice Booker has demonstrated his commitment to
3 teaching the Gospel, witnessing Christ through word and deed, and addressing the physical,
4 psychological, intellectual, and spiritual needs of others; and
5 WHEREAS, he was called by the Lord in 1992, and in February of 1994, Pastor Booker was
6 ordained in the gospel ministry by his grandfather, the late Reverend Walter Booker Jr.; and
7 WHEREAS, God in his infinite wisdom placed him as pastor of the New Hope Baptist
8 Church of Harlem, in January 1997, one month after the retiring of his grandfather; and
9 WHEREAS, his vision and direction helped New Hope Baptist Church grow in size and
10 influence, uplifting the community like the light of Bethlehem and serving as a spiritual
11 leader and place for fellowship; and
12 WHEREAS, Pastor Booker served the congregation of New Hope Baptist Church for 23
13 years; and
