14 WHEREAS, on February 8, 2020, Broadway Baptist Church in Augusta, Georgia, called
15 Pastor Booker as their eleventh Pastor; and
16 WHEREAS, Pastor Booker has lead Broadway Baptist Church in a total renovation and
17 upgrade project, birthed several new ministries, and has established the Missional purpose
18 as "Empowering People to Impact the World"; and
19 WHEREAS, he presently serves as President of the Baptist Ministers Conference of Augusta,
20 is a Board member of the Downtown Development Authority of Augusta, and is President
21 and CEO of South Augusta Community Development Corporation, Inc; an
22 WHEREAS, whether the task is preparing a sermon, visiting the sick, counseling the
23 troubled, baptizing a new believer, or acting as a theologian, educator, administrator, or
24 humanitarian, Pastor Booker serves as a shining example of God's righteous path; and
25 WHEREAS, the unmatched spiritual assistance offered by Pastor Booker is a source of
26 strength and direction for persons in all walks of life; and
27 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this enduring example of God's message
28 of peace and love be recognized and congratulated for his innumerable good works rendered
29 on behalf of persons in need.
30 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
31 the members of this body recognize and commend Reverend Anthony Maurice Booker and
32 extend best wishes for many more years of successful fellowship and leadership
